                              <condition key="deficient">
                                The sewing is completely damaged on the spine thus it was heavily reparaired with different kind of thread.
                                The lower board is broken in two halves held together by a leather string passing through the holes.
                                Quire 1 and quire 2 are stained with dirt along the lower part showing signs of intense use.
                                There are tears on the margins. The parchment is of a good manifacture. Tears occurred during the manifacture were repaired using vegetable thread.
                                On fol. 18v there is a wide white stain, probably a starch based adhesive.
                              </condition>

